#
# Per-rig overrides for the ain subprocess.
#
# Sourced from config/ainconf.tcl at the end of its startup, so the
# dserv_ain module is loaded and ainStart/ainSetNchan have already run.
# Use this file for anything rig-specific: different acquisition rate,
# non-default channel count, signal inversions, or a custom dpoint
# prefix if this rig wants to isolate its ain output.
#

# Example: lower the acquisition rate from 1 kHz to 500 Hz.
# Ain is already running at 1 ms interval when this file is sourced,
# so ainStop/ainStart must be used to change it.
#
# ainStop
# ainStart 2

# Example: invert channel 1 (signal maps 4095..0 instead of 0..4095).
# Useful if the pot is wired "backwards" from what the experiment
# expects.
#
# ainInvertSignal 1 1

# Example: change the output prefix so this rig's ain module publishes
# to "foo/vals" instead of "ain/vals". Leave commented out to keep the
# default (which is what the slider subprocess subscribes to).
#
# ainSetPrefix foo

# Print a summary of the resulting state so the log clearly shows what
# this rig is configured for.
puts "ain (local): [ainGetInfo]"
